des:
You can simply ask Alexa to control your ABRA lighting or other devices:
(1) Download the "Intermatic ABRA" app in App Store or Google Play store, then register an account;
(2) Configure the devices in the "Intermatic ABRA" app and re-name them for easy identification, like "table lamp";
(3) Download Amazon Alexa app from the App Store, Google Play store, or Amazon app market and use it to configure your Echo device;
(4) Search for the "ABRA" skill from the Alexa app skills category;
(5) Enable the "ABRA" skill, and you'll be navigated to the login page. Follow the instructions on the page to complete linking;
(6) Now the setup is finished. You can now enjoy Alexa voice control for your ABRA smart home devices:
Alexa, turn on the table lamp.
Alexa, turn off the table lamp.
Alexa, set the bedroom light to 50%.
Alexa, brighten the bedroom light to 50%.
Alexa, dim the bedroom light to 50%.
Alexa, set bedroom light to green.
